Reminder :
1. Git Pull all latest changes from main branch before start any new changes
2. Branch out (Create new branch) from main branch
3. Do code at that new branch
4. Git Commit & Push to that new branch
5. Create Pull Request when features are ready
6. Merge to main branch via pull request
7. During pull request, if there is conflict, pull latest changes from main branch, then merge main to your branch, resolve conflict locally, then only push to remote and merge via pull request
8. Delete remote branch at github

Use bash 5.1.16
Run /usr/local/bin/bash in terminal